\subsection{Composition Operator Evolution}
Three composition operators were systematically evaluated.
Simple vector addition exhibited anchor dominance ($F_{AB}\approx F_B$).
Pointwise complex multiplication produced severe spectral de-correlation
($\cos(F_{AB},F_A)\approx-0.10$, $\cos(F_{AB},F_B)\approx-0.03$).
The normalized-sum midpoint operator resolved both failure modes:
$\cos(F_{AB},F_A)=\cos(F_{AB},F_B)=0.786$.

